com.vector.cfg.automation.scripting.base

Interface IScriptTaskType

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IUserMessage
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IScriptTaskType.IApplicationScriptTaskType, IScriptTaskType.IInitScriptTaskType, IScriptTaskType.IProjectScriptTaskType

    @PublishedApi(value=ADDITIONS_ALLOWED)
 @PublishedApiDomain(value=AUTOMATION_IF)
 @ThreadSafe
public interface IScriptTaskType
extends IUserMessage
    IScriptTaskType defines the possible execution point of the IScriptTask and the arguments passed to the IScriptTask during execution.

    The DaVinci Configurator provides multiple task types for different execution points in the system. The types are defined in different classes:

    • com.vector.cfg.automation.scripting.api.EDefaultProjectScriptTaskType
    • com.vector.cfg.automation.scripting.api.EDefaultApplicationScriptTaskType

    Every IScriptTask instance has to defined the argument types and the return type of the script task. See the specific task type for the correct type information.

    The are two categories of IScriptTaskType:

    • IScriptTaskType.IProjectScriptTaskType: Task which are only executable with a loaded project
    • IScriptTaskType.IApplicationScriptTaskType: Tasks which are executable with a running Configuration, but not necessary a loaded project.

    All method parameters and return values must be non-null unless documented otherwise.

    This is a value class, which means the implementation check for value equality (see equals, hashCode).

      • isExecutable

        @PublishedMethod
default boolean isExecutable(IScriptTask scriptTask,
                                               INotExecutableReasonBuilder reasonBuilder,
                                               java.lang.Object[] args)
        Checks if the passed scriptTask is executable with the passed arguments according to the IScriptTaskType.

        This can be used, that a special IScriptTaskType, can determine the execution by the runtime arguments passed to the IScriptTask.

        Parameters:
        scriptTask - the script task to check for. The task must have this task type
        reasonBuilder - the INotExecutableReasonBuilder to add the reason, why it is not executable
        args - the args to the IScriptTask
        Returns:
        true, if the IScriptTask is executable
